        <updateDate>2023-07-28T20:12:37Z</updateDate>
        <cdata>
          <text>&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Increasing Investor Opportunities Act &lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This bill allows a closed-end fund&amp;#8212;a portfolio of pooled assets with a limited number of shares traded on an exchange&amp;#8212;to increase its investment in private investment funds. &lt;/p&gt;</text>
        </cdata>
      </summary>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>07</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2023-12-12</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Reported to House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2024-07-25T18:31:32Z</updateDate>
        <cdata>
          <text>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Increasing Investor Opportunities Act &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This bill allows a closed-end fund—a portfolio of pooled assets with a limited number of shares traded on an exchange—to increase its investment in private investment funds.&amp;nbsp;The Securities and Exchange Commission is prohibited from limiting the sale or listing of securities of a closed-end fund that invests in private investment funds. This bill also apples to a closed-end company treated as a business development company.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;!--tinycomments|2.1|data:application/json;base64,--&gt;</text>
        </cdata>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
